-- Electronic Arts loss wider than expected
-- 
-- Tue Jul 29, 2008 5:16pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/29/us-electronicarts-idUSN2937091920080729

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - Video game maker Electronic Arts Inc ERTS.O posted a larger-than-expected quarterly loss on Tuesday and its shares fell nearly 3 percent. 

 The net loss was $95 million, or 30 cents a share, compared with a year-ago loss of $132 million, or 42 cents a share, it said. The Redwood City, California-based company posted an adjusted loss of 42 cents per share, worse than Wall Street's average target of a 35 cent loss, according to Reuters Estimates. Net revenue rose to $804 million from $395 million a year ago. Shares of EA fell 2.7 percent in after-hours trade to $46.10 from a Nasdaq close of $47.40. (Reporting by  Jennifer Martinez ; Editing by  Braden Reddall )